_comment=' LM Aero Change: 20080430 rms - Item #082. Removed post space for the <def&gt; output. This causes a single-spaced two-column table. LM Aero has been using <deflist&gt; tables in this way since 5.2 M030 was not coded properly. Since there is no other option other than to build two-column tables, the alternative is to add an attribute to the <deflist&gt; element for spacing and use the default of "single". For now, it is off.&#13;&#13; 5.3 M060 CPA 1.4 F000 code
<postsp minimum="6pt" nominal="6pt" maximum="6pt" condit="discard" priority="high"&gt;&#13;&#13; 5.3 M060 CPA 1.4 F000 code
<postsp minimum="6pt" nominal="6pt" maximum="6pt" condit="discard" priority="high"&gt;'>
